UID:260223CzpS6UY-20anL62pDtLgmw
DESCRIPTION:March 7-8\, 11am to 4pm both days\n\nMarch 7-8\, 2026 11:00 am
  - 4:00 pm each day\n\nJoin Us for Wine Road's Annual Barrel Tasting. The 
 Longest Running Wine Event in California.\n\nCelebrate one of Sonoma Count
 y's most cherished wine traditions at Wine Road's Annual Barrel Tasting. N
 ow in its 48th year\, this iconic event brings together 50 wineries across
  Northern Sonoma County for a tasting experience focused entirely on the P
 ast\, Present\, and Future of wine.\n\nBarrel Tasting is not a food-pairin
 g or themed event-it's all about the wine and how it evolves over time. Ta
 ste a current vintage\, compare it to the same wine still aging in the bar
 rel\, and savor the depth and complexity of select library wines. It's a r
 are opportunity to explore the winemaking journey side by side\, straight 
 from the source.\n\nMeet the winemakers\, step into the cellar\, and exper
 ience the heart and soul of Sonoma County winemaking up close. Come ready 
 to taste\, learn\, and have fun-Barrel Tasting happens just once a year\, 
 and it's not to be missed.\n\nTicket Prices:\n\n$50 Weekend - This ticket 
 is good for both Saturday and Sunday\, there will not be a 1-day ticket op
 tion.\n\n$10 Designated Driver
LOCATION:50 Participating Wineries in Northern Sonoma County
URL:http://www.wineroad.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
