SUMMARY:Virgins to Villains - Live Theatre at THE 222
DTSTART;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T190000
DTEND;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T190000
UID:260219B_YEGFjzVUGcywl5Kz9F7w
DESCRIPTION:Robin Goodrin Nordli returns to THE 222 in this witty\, insigh
 tful\, and revealing one-woman show. This Oregon Shakespeare Festival vet
 eran actor draws from her experiences of performing in 61 productions of 
 30 different plays by William Shakespeare. From the Bard’s innocent virg
 ins to his vindictive villains\, Robin masterfully explores her own life 
 journey through the prism of her relationship with Shakespeare’s female
  characters.\n\nTouching\, powerful and entertaining.— Dangerous Common
  Sense\n\nSponsored by Kate & Dennis Abbe\, Randy Varney & John King\, an
 d Michael & Janet Verlander\n\nTheatre - Programmed by Aldo Billingslea an
 d Amy Kossow\n\nTHE 222 / 222 Healdsburg Avenue / Healdsburg CA
