BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Monoprints: Drawing & Printing Abstraction Two-day workshop
DTSTART;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T110000
DTEND;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T160000
UID:260110cAWJpF7ndEOBtbGkWTPhag
DESCRIPTION:**Monoprinting** is a unique expression of printmaking typica
 lly painterly in effect\, made by applying or painting ink to an historica
 lly\, copper etching plate.  In contemporary work it can vary from zinc t
 o acrylic or a gel plate\, or no plate at all. In contrast to other printi
 ng processes\, mono-printing creates one final image.  However\, it is po
 ssible to create a “ghost” print (or lighter print) after the final im
 age - but it is its own image\, not identical to the original.  \n\nIn t
 his class\, we will use the idea of experimenting\, and using drawing\, tr
 acing\, stencil and the printing presses available to us at the Art Escape
  to create abstract images from nature and  using recycled materials.  T
 hese found materials create all kinds of markings\, shapes and images - as
  they make their way through the press.  Botanicals can compliment the st
 encils and create openings for more texture\, shapes\, and imagery to crea
 te layered pieces through multiple runs through the press.  When peeling 
 back the paper for the look\, it is the surprise element that keeps me com
 ing back to this process.  This process also works well with other printm
 aking processes.  Using materials like Tyvek that can be traced or cut in
 to shapes and images\, we can layer these elements onto the plate or paper
  and then put through the press over and over again creating repeat images
 .  While creating interesting artful images that are so intriguing\, they
  might even be considered poetic.
LOCATION:Art Escape
URL:https://artescapesonoma.jumbula.com/Spring2026/MonoprintsDrawingPrinti
 ngAbstraction
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:American Red Cross Adult and Pediatric First-Aid/CPR/AED Class (Bl
 ended)
