BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Unknown Wayne Thiebaud: Passionate Printmaker
DTSTART;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T100000
DTEND;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T160000
UID:251217jxfjhE_DykyEYOmIwkhWOQ
DESCRIPTION:Wayne Thiebaud's lushly painted still life's of cakes\, pies\,
  and gumball machines are icons of modern American Art. But there is anoth
 er large body of Thiebaud's art that is relatively unknown: his prints. Th
 iebaud had a life-long passion for printmaking --- his first print was mad
 e of pieces of linoleum he ran through the wringer of his mother's washing
  machine! And he continued making prints until well into his 90s. This exh
 ibition will highlight Thiebaud's printed artwork spanning 6 decades\, exp
 loring common themes and subject matter and the artist's unusual working m
 ethod. In addition\, the exhibition will focus on Thiebaud's extraordinary
  relationship with his New York gallerist Allan Stone. Stone gave Thiebaud
  his first major exhibition and continued to represent him for over 45 yea
 rs\, a legendary relationship in the art world. Also join us for a wrap-ar
 ound program lecture on Thursday\, January 29th\, 2026 to hear Wayne Thieb
 aud: The Whole Story from Linda Loveland Reid\, an OLLI instructor for Son
 oma State and Dominican Universities. In this lecture\, we will be discuss
 ing Wayne Thieband's versatile and dynamic personality who brough us not o
 nly delicious dessert paintings\, but also landscapes and figures. In this
  discussion\, we will look at his famous works\, review his life\, and lea
 rn about his extraordinary printmaking skills that are highlighted in the 
 SebArts exhibit. General Admission Tickets are $15.00. Free Public Entry D
 ays Are January 23rd and 24th\, and February 21st and 22nd. SebArts Member
 s are granted free entry\, and students get $5 off per ticket. Purchase yo
 ur tickets before the event\, or at the door. To schedule a docent led gro
 up tour of 6 or more\, email RWynne@sebarts.org.\n\nDate and Time: Saturda
 y January 10\, 2026 at 10:00 am to Sunday March 8\, 2026 at 4:00 pm
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center For The Arts
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/thiebaud
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
