BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Overeaters Anonymous (OA) Newcomer Meeting
DTSTART;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T094500
DTEND;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T101500
UID:260212PRHqaMVtYkO8CDZNoNMmCQ
DESCRIPTION:**Is Food a Problem for You? You Are Not Alone.**\n\nOvereater
 s Anonymous (OA) is a fellowship of people who support each other in recov
 ering from compulsive eating and food behaviors. If you feel you have a pr
 oblem with food\, OA welcomes you—no matter what your background\, belie
 fs\, or eating habits. \n\nWe hold an in-person newcomer meeting on first
 \, second and fourth **Saturdays of the month from 9:45 - 10:15 AM at** 
 ​**Unitarian Universalist Congregation of Marin\, 240 Channing Way\, San
  Rafael CA 94903**. Contact: Sue M. 415-298-6792​. You may view all Nor
 th Bay OA in-person and online meetings at https://www.northbayoa.org/meet
 ings.html\n\nIn OA\, members experience **spiritual\, emotional\, and phys
 ical recovery** by practicing the **Twelve Steps** and living by their spi
 ritual principles—one day at a time.\n\nOA is **not** a diet club or cal
 orie-counting program.\n\nMembers have different plans of eating.\n\nOA do
 es **not** endorse any specific food plan. \n\nIf food is causing problem
 s in your life\, you don’t have to struggle alone. Recovery is possible\
 , and help is available.\n\n**Visit:** https://www.northbayoa.org/\n\n**Fi
 nd a meeting:** https://www.northbayoa.org/meetings.html
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalist Congregation of Marin
URL:https://www.northbayoa.org/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
