BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jeffrey Halford & The Healers
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T173000
DTEND;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T000000
UID:260225h6JCUD5Xf0KCO2imlx_ZKg
DESCRIPTION:Of the many marks of genius associated with rock n’ roll gre
 atness\, the knack for surrounding oneself with transformational talent lo
 oms especially large\, with The Rolling Stones being perhaps the most nota
 ble example. Jeffrey Halford treads a poetic rootsy path on his latest rel
 ease\, SOUL CRUSADE\, combining a bulletproof collection of songs inspired
  by gospel\, folk\, soul\, and blues\, with a formidable roster of musical
  contributors. The result is one of Halford’s most approachable and easy
 -grooving.\n\nHis latest album release\, SOUL CRUSADE\, is the follow-up t
 o the critically acclaimed record WEST TOWARDS SOUTH. The album came out i
 n Europe on Continental Song City\, debuted in September at \\#2\, and the
 n undisputedly reached \\#1 in October 2022 and stayed in the chart for fo
 ur months. \n\nJEFFREY HALFORD & THE HEALERS are gearing up for their eigh
 th European tour in September and October 2025\, bringing their signature 
 blend of raw rock ‘n’ roll\, country\, and soul back to the stage. But
  this tour isn’t just another run—it marks the 25th anniversary of KER
 OSENE\, the album \\(release date Friday\, August 29th\, 2025\\) that put 
 Halford on the map as a true Americana troubadour.
LOCATION:Redwood Cafe
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107986520?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:In Her Power
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T160000
UID:260225Pe33Dh3R6UuBObizUvtHKw
DESCRIPTION:In Her Power\n\nA Collaboration by Priscila Soares & JeanCheri
 e\n\nIn Her Power is a group exhibition celebrating women’s presence\, s
 trength\, and creative expression. Anchored by a collaborative\, life-size
  sculptural work by Priscila Soares and JeanCherie\, the exhibition brings
  together works by women artists exploring power as something lived\, embo
 died\, and deeply personal.\n\nAt the heart of the gallery stands a mounta
 in lioness woman — a guardian figure shaped by two artists working toget
 her\, each bringing her own voice\, materials\, and vision. Surrounding th
 is central work\, invited artists contribute pieces that reflect their own
  relationship to power\, resilience\, intuition\, and selfhood.\n\nRather 
 than offering a single definition\, In Her Power invites viewers to witnes
 s many expressions of strength — quiet and fierce\, ancestral and contem
 porary\, individual and shared. It is both a celebration of women artists 
 and an invitation to step into presence\, creativity\, and connection.\n\n
 Opening Reception:\n\nMarch 1\, 12–4pm\n\nGallery Hours:\n\nSundays in M
 arch\, 12–4pm\n\nLocation:\n\nMare Island Art Studios\n\n110 Pintado St.
 \n\nVallejo\, CA
LOCATION:Mare Island Art Studios
URL:https://mareislandartstudios.com/events/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
