BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Online: Unshakeable Peace Rooted in Earth-Based Practices
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T130000
UID:260214ySmLml0Hckeq0deYVhUS_A
DESCRIPTION:with Carol Cano\, MA and Ayya Santacitta\n\nIn a world of cons
 tant change and uncertainty\, this half-day of mindfulness practice offers
  an invitation to return to what is steady and reliable. Drawing from Fore
 st Buddhist teachings and earth-based awareness\, we will cultivate a peac
 e that does not depend on conditions. A peace that arises from being fully
  present\, embodied\, and grounded.\n\nThrough sitting and walking meditat
 ion\, and periods of silence\, we will explore the body as part of the liv
 ing earth and awareness as a refuge that is always available. Rather than 
 striving for calm\, the practice invites us to rest in what already holds 
 us—moment by moment\, breath by breath.\n\nThis is offered as a time to 
 slow down\, listen deeply\, and reconnect with the unshakeable peace withi
 n our own hearts.
LOCATION:Spirit Rock Meditation Center
URL:https://spirit-rock.secure.retreat.guru/program/unshakeable-peace-root
 ed-in-earth-based-practices-anchored-in-awareness-cc1h26/?lang=en
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
