BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Dido and Aeneas by Purcell together with Pagliacci by Leoncavallo
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T150000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T170000
UID:260124gjD0ePLMwEG7bh9yK8ePRA
DESCRIPTION:Verismo Opera presents Dido and Aeneas by Purcell together wit
 h Pagliacci by Leoncavallo\n\nFree Admission. Become a member to support o
 ur new free admission policy.  Membership will be good for a year from pu
 rchase and will entitle members to early seating \\(before non-members\\) 
 for performances.\n\n Stage Directors: Kristin Lund and Jennifer Rineman
  \n\nConductors: Jonathan Khuner and Paul Schrage\n\nChamber Orchestra wi
 th English Supertitles \n\nIn association with Mira Theatre Guild\n\nFor
  company information and to purchase memberships visit www.verismoopera.o
 rg\n\nDido and Aeneas is a monumental English Baroque opera masterpiece.
   The story is based on Virgil’s The Aeneid and tells the tale of lov
 e and tragedy between Dido\, Queen of Carthage\, and the Trojan hero Aenea
 s.  This beloved gem includes stunning choruses\, duos\, trios and the ic
 onic aria "Dido’s Lament".  In contrast to Dido and Aeneas’ measured 
 passions\, Pagliacci is full of uncontrollable passion\, jealousy\, trag
 edy\, murder\, and betrayal.  Laugh and weep with Canio as he sings "Vest
 i la giubba" \\(the clown who cries behind his makeup\\).\n\nMira Theatre 
 Guild\, 51 Daniels Avenue\, Vallejo\, CA 94590\n\n- February 21\, 2026 \\(
 Saturday 7:00pm\\)\n\n- February 22\, 2026 \\(Sunday 3:00pm\\)\n\n- Februa
 ry 28\, 2026 \\(Saturday 7:00pm\\)\n\n- March 1\, 2026 \\(Sunday 3:00pm\\
 )\n\n- March 7\, 2026  \\(Saturday 7:00pm\\)\n\n- March 8\, 2026  \\(Sun
 day 3:00pm\\)
LOCATION:Mira Theatre Guild
URL:http://www.verismoopera.org
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Monoprints: Drawing & Printing Abstraction Two-day workshop
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T160000
UID:260113ypAZmoYJa0OzGS5q2UIXGw
DESCRIPTION:**Monoprinting** is a unique expression of printmaking typica
 lly painterly in effect\, made by applying or painting ink to an historica
 lly\, copper etching plate.  In contemporary work it can vary from zinc t
 o acrylic or a gel plate\, or no plate at all. In contrast to other printi
 ng processes\, mono-printing creates one final image.  However\, it is po
 ssible to create a “ghost” print (or lighter print) after the final im
 age - but it is its own image\, not identical to the original.  \n\nIn t
 his class\, we will use the idea of experimenting\, and using drawing\, tr
 acing\, stencil and the printing presses available to us at the Art Escape
  to create abstract images from nature and  using recycled materials.  T
 hese found materials create all kinds of markings\, shapes and images - as
  they make their way through the press.  Botanicals can compliment the st
 encils and create openings for more texture\, shapes\, and imagery to crea
 te layered pieces through multiple runs through the press.  When peeling 
 back the paper for the look\, it is the surprise element that keeps me com
 ing back to this process.  This process also works well with other printm
 aking processes.  Using materials like Tyvek that can be traced or cut in
 to shapes and images\, we can layer these elements onto the plate or paper
  and then put through the press over and over again creating repeat images
 .  While creating interesting artful images that are so intriguing\, they
  might even be considered poetic.
LOCATION:Art Escape
URL:https://artescapesonoma.jumbula.com/Spring2026/MonoprintsDrawingPrinti
 ngAbstraction
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Flora & Fauna - Watercolor Course with Hannah Day at Bohemian Flow
 ers Farm
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T130000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T160000
UID:260113R7Nw-kTqX0m7Q7po_ynwVA
DESCRIPTION:In this 4 week course\, participants will learn a unique appro
 ach to watercolor\, intended to alleviate the frustration that many experi
 ence when learning this beautiful yet challenging medium. The class will f
 ocus on strengthening one’s observational skills\, giving the artist a f
 oundation off of which to build their paintings in a step by step layering
  process\, that trains the artist to see value and color\n\nOur subject ma
 tter will be flora and fauna - a sampling of plants and animals. These sub
 jects are great for beginners and experienced artists alike\; their organi
 c shapes make them forgiving drawing subjects\, but their beauty can be a 
 muse for life. \n\nThis class will work both from photographs and from li
 fe\, practicing observational drawing in addition to watercolor technique.
  With 4 class sessions\, participants will have the opportunity to develop
  their skills and build muscle memory with a medium that often feels like 
 it has a mind of its own. \n\nAll materials provided.\n\nLocation: Bohemi
 an Flowers Farm\, 121 Bohemian Hwy\, Freestone\, CA\n\nDates: Four Sundays
  - March 8\, 15\, 22\, 29\n\nTime: 1 - 4 pm\n\nAges: Adults\n\nSkill Level
 s: All Levels
LOCATION:Bohemian Flowers Farm
URL:https://www.hannahdrawstrees.com/flora-fauna-register
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Bonsai Show: Bonsai & Blossoms
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T170000
UID:260108BsrwxmyAbUS8gy6bRAvrEg
DESCRIPTION:January 9–March 22\, 2026\n\nStep into a wonderland of bloom
 ing miniature trees to marvel at the living art of bonsai and the season
 ’s first flowers. Then stroll through our Asian Woodland to admire maje
 stic magnolias\, cherries\, and camellias in bloom\, or join a tour or pro
 gram to explore this timeless craft.\n\nThis year’s all-new presentation
  by the skilled artisans of the Redwood Empire Bonsai Society \\(REBS\\) h
 ighlights the grace and vitality of flowering bonsai—trees and shrubs tr
 ained to bloom in exquisite proportion to their diminutive scale. Delicate
  plum\, azalea\, camellia\, cherry\, and apricot bonsai take center stag
 e\, their blossoms appearing just as winter begins to yield to spring. The
 se early bloomers symbolize hope and renewal—reminding us that beauty an
 d resilience can emerge even in the coldest months.\n\nThe exhibition also
  draws inspiration from hanami\, the centuries-old Japanese tradition of 
 celebrating the fleeting beauty of blossoms. The Garden invites visitors t
 o participate in this art of flower appreciation through Hanami Strolls
 —guided walks through the Garden’s Asian woodland where early-blooming
  magnolias\, cherries\, and camellias offer their own ephemeral display.
LOCATION:Sonoma Botanical Garden
URL:https://sonomabg.org/visit/bonsai-and-blossoms/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Unknown Wayne Thiebaud: Passionate Printmaker
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T160000
UID:251217mGrK-6iwaky5OgWJMjcQxg
DESCRIPTION:Wayne Thiebaud's lushly painted still life's of cakes\, pies\,
  and gumball machines are icons of modern American Art. But there is anoth
 er large body of Thiebaud's art that is relatively unknown: his prints. Th
 iebaud had a life-long passion for printmaking --- his first print was mad
 e of pieces of linoleum he ran through the wringer of his mother's washing
  machine! And he continued making prints until well into his 90s. This exh
 ibition will highlight Thiebaud's printed artwork spanning 6 decades\, exp
 loring common themes and subject matter and the artist's unusual working m
 ethod. In addition\, the exhibition will focus on Thiebaud's extraordinary
  relationship with his New York gallerist Allan Stone. Stone gave Thiebaud
  his first major exhibition and continued to represent him for over 45 yea
 rs\, a legendary relationship in the art world. Also join us for a wrap-ar
 ound program lecture on Thursday\, January 29th\, 2026 to hear Wayne Thieb
 aud: The Whole Story from Linda Loveland Reid\, an OLLI instructor for Son
 oma State and Dominican Universities. In this lecture\, we will be discuss
 ing Wayne Thieband's versatile and dynamic personality who brough us not o
 nly delicious dessert paintings\, but also landscapes and figures. In this
  discussion\, we will look at his famous works\, review his life\, and lea
 rn about his extraordinary printmaking skills that are highlighted in the 
 SebArts exhibit. General Admission Tickets are $15.00. Free Public Entry D
 ays Are January 23rd and 24th\, and February 21st and 22nd. SebArts Member
 s are granted free entry\, and students get $5 off per ticket. Purchase yo
 ur tickets before the event\, or at the door. To schedule a docent led gro
 up tour of 6 or more\, email RWynne@sebarts.org.\n\nDate and Time: Saturda
 y January 10\, 2026 at 10:00 am to Sunday March 8\, 2026 at 4:00 pm
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center For The Arts
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/thiebaud
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Future of Bass Awardee\, Bass Phenom Mohini Dey Quartet
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T193000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T220000
UID:251126_8jjDBPAw0yUYnmlVlW9ig
DESCRIPTION:Mohini Dey is a renowned bass guitarist\, arranger\, producer 
 and vocalist who has gained international recognition for her extraordinar
 y talent and versatility. With her unique style and impeccable technique\,
  she has collaborated with numerous renowned artists and performed on pres
 tigious stages around the world. She is a 27-year-old bass guitarist from 
 Mumbai\, India.\n\nShe has been described as the “Most Successful Musici
 an UNDER30” By ForbesIndia. She has been working professionally in the m
 usic industry for the past 18 years meaning that she started working profe
 ssionally when she was only 9 years old. She is the only female bassist to
  rank within the 'Top 10 Bassists in the 21st Century' on Music Radar. She
  has over 20 million views collectively on YouTube\, 406k followers on Ins
 tagram and 183K subscribers on YouTube and 201K followers on Facebook. She
  is currently the bassist for Willow Smith. She has worked with artists li
 ke Steve Vai\, Zakir Hussain\, Quincy Jones\, Vinnie Colauita\, Stanley Cl
 arke\, Jordan Rudess\, Mike Stern\, Dean Brown\, A R Rahman\, Sivamani\, M
 arco Minneman\, Gary Willis\, Dave Weckl\, Tony Macalpine\, Stu Hamm\, Pli
 ni\, Louiz Banks\, Guthrie Govan\, Ranjit Barot\, Chad Wackerman\, Chad Sm
 ith\, Simon Phillips\, Prasanna\, Gergo Borlai\, Victor Wooten\, Federico 
 Malaman\, Darwin\, Niladri Kumar\, Stu Hamm\, Sivamani\, Bumblefoot\, etc 
 many more artists. Some Indian singers and directors that she has worked w
 ith are Salim Sulaiman\, Clinton Cerejo\, Neeti Mohan\, Amit Trivedi\, Ben
 ny Dayal\, Sunidhi Chauhan\, Shreya Ghoshal\, Arijit Singh\, Shalmali Khol
 gade\, Sonu Kakkar\, Shilpa Rao\, Vishal-Shekar\, Gurdasman\, etc She has 
 also been featured in magazines like Vogue\, ForbesIndiaUnder30\, NoTreble
 \, RadarMusic\, Bass Professor\, Bass Magazine\, BassQuaterly\, Rollingsto
 ne\, JazzInIndia\, ParentCircle\, RadioAndMusic\, Platform\, Femina\, Hind
 u\, NewIndianExpress\, Verve and many other articles in newspapers like DN
 A\, The Indian Express\, Hindustan Times\, Mid-Day\, Mumbai Mirror\, The T
 imes of India\, Bombay Times\, etc.\n\nShe has played on Jimmy Fallon Show
  and Tiny Desk NPR and tours with Willow Smith.\n\nMohini will be joined b
 y:\n\nMarco Cirigliano: Drums/Voc\n\nDaniel Szebenyi: Keys\n\nJonathan Mon
 es: Sax\n\nURLs:\n\nInstagram: https://go.evvnt.com/3313410-3?pid=6630\n\n
 Facebook: https://go.evvnt.com/3313410-4?pid=6630\n\nInstagram: https://go
 .evvnt.com/3313410-5?pid=6630\n\nArtists: Mohini Dey- Bass and Vocals\, Ma
 rco Cirigliano- Percussion\, Daniel Szebenyi - Keyes\, Jonathan Mones- Sax
LOCATION:Music and Minds at The Dance Palace
URL:https://www.musicandminds.org/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
