BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stella Swings Ella
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T180000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T180000
UID:260303ec4kcZoji06aAnblUf2RBw
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the timeless music of Ella Fitzgerald\, the First La
 dy of Song\, whose nearly 60-year career helped define American jazz. From
  her swing-era brilliance at the Savoy Ballroom to her pioneering bebop im
 provisation and iconic songbook recordings\, Ella’s voice elevated the w
 orks of Cole Porter\, Duke Ellington\, and George Gershwin into enduring c
 lassics. Her later years saw her captivating audiences worldwide with eleg
 ance\, joy\, and unmatched musicality. Bay Area vocalist Stella Heath\, pr
 aised for The Billie Holiday Project and Stella Meets Nat\, takes on Ella
 ’s legendary repertoire in Stella Swings Ella. Backed by an all-star ban
 d featuring Ian Scherer \\(guitar\\)\, Daniel Fabricant \\(bass\\)\, Robby
  Elfman \\(saxophone/clarinet\\)\, and Spike Klein \\(drums\\)\, this even
 ing of vintage jazz from the 1930s–1950s promises a vibrant\, soulful tr
 ibute to one of music’s greatest voices. TICKETS: PURCHASE IN ADVANCE AN
 D SAVE! Zones A & B ensure a seat. Zone C has limited seating\, plus stand
 ing room. Zone A  $33 Zone B $28 Zone C $23 \\(does not guarantee seating\
 \) Tickets at the door $33 \\(Zone C only\\) Doors open 5:30pm.  Our kitch
 en serves our All New Menu from the time doors open until end of intermiss
 ion. \\(Kitchen available only at events with 60 or more advance tickets s
 old\\)
LOCATION:The California
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/34018562674426045/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
