BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hook and Ladder Vineyards and Winery
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T123000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T123000
UID:251219cuQszsyRfEO4A_X9L1UxXQ
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:Hook & Ladder Vineyards & Winery
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107647185?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:March Month of Flowers Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260309T000000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260309T120000
UID:260306HrlMbzWnOUWwOuh0pL9pxQ
DESCRIPTION:Starting March 1st begins the "March Month of Flowers Challeng
 e" \\(online\\). \n\nYou'll receive a list of prompts for every day in Mar
 ch. \n\nCreate an art piece related to the prompt.\n\nShare in our privat
 e Facebook group.\n\nBe inspired and give inspiration to others.\n\nOnly $
 5\, so everyone can join and share in this creative adventure!\n\nMarch Mo
 nth of Flowers Challenge is here to give you a creative outlet\, some st
 ructure\, and respite from your brain. \n\nWhen you pick up a brush\, pen
 \, or pencil \\(thread\, clay\, fabric…\\)\, your brain gets a rest and 
 becomes more alive and flexible. The world around you becomes more alive\
 ; you pick up on shades\, details\, and patterns all around you. Your in
 tuition gets stronger. And fear lessens\, anxiety fades\, and curiosity gr
 ows. You stop worrying about making mistakes\, and instead\, you find the
  freedom to simply create
URL:https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
