SUMMARY:Become a Volunteer Seabird Monitor
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260309T180000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260309T193000
UID:251105VhDdLgfFB0y3QE6KhwfCcA
DESCRIPTION:Join us to learn the skills you need to become a Volunteer Se
 abird Monitor with Stewards of the Coast and Redwoods.\n\nNo experience is
  necessary.\n\nStewards’ Seabird Monitoring program began in 2013\, tha
 nks to funding from the Bureau of Land Management. Stewards is partnering 
 with the California Coastal National Monument \\(CCNM\\) to monitor breedi
 ng seabirds off the Sonoma Coast and is a local Chapter of the Seabird Pr
 otection Network.\n\nInstructor: Hollis Bewley \\(Seabird Monitoring Progr
 am Coordinator\\)\n\nThis is a two-part training:\n\nPart 1 of the trainin
 g on zoom Monday March 9th from 6-7:30pm Seabird Monitoring Training part 
 1 Join Zoom Meeting: https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84074028922\n\nPart 2 of t
 he training on Thursday\, March 19 from 9:30 AM to noon is an experiential
  training at a location meeting at the Bodega Head East parking lot. We
