BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"You're My Neighbor" Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T090000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T180000
UID:260227pIwLHrmtc0aOnx_PmiZwIA
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:CRESCENDO - LIVE MUSIC concert presented by Solano College Music
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T203000
UID:260225lGU4gP_JnU2VHWyq5olgIg
DESCRIPTION:Explore and enjoy music by women and Black composers with Sola
 no College Music at CRESCENDO!\n\nAbout the show: CRESCENDO is a fun\, fam
 ily-friendly\, and educational concert featuring Black and women composers
  in honor of Black History Month \\(February\\) and Women’s History Mont
 h \\(March\\). Come enjoy live music performed by the SCC Chamber Choir an
 d SCC Chamber Orchestra! Between songs\, you’ll learn about historic com
 posers like Florence Price\, the first African-American woman to have a pi
 ece played by a major orchestra\, and Scott Joplin\, dubbed the “King of
  Ragtime” who was posthumously awarded a Pulitzer Price for his accompli
 shments. \n\nTuesday\, March 10 at 7 p.m.\n\nAbout 1.5 hours\n\nFREE entr
 y and parking!\n\nSolano College Theatre\n\nBuilding 1200\n\n4000 Suisun V
 alley Road\n\nFairfield\, CA 94534\n\nAbout the producer: Solano College M
 usic is dedicated to educating the next generations of musicians\, singers
 \, and composers in the performance and development of great music! We pro
 duce concerts that contribute meaningfully to the culture\, education\, an
 d entertainment of our Solano County community.
LOCATION:Solano College Theatre
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/839256989130082/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
