BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:George Kahumoku Jr & Led Kaapana & Sonny Lim
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260311T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260311T000000
UID:260224qedK-1Mybk-DKTj0Dc2r8w
DESCRIPTION:Masters of Hawaiian Music features three of the most popular m
 usicians from Maui’s renowned “Slack Key Show.” 4-time Grammy winner
 \, slack key guitar master George Kahumoku Jr\, National Heritage Fellow L
 ed Kaapana\, whose picking style of slack key guitar is unrivaled\, and So
 nny Lim\, who plays both lap steel \\(invented in Hawai‘i\\) and slack k
 ey guitar. Together they share Hawai‘i’s unique slack key \\(open tuni
 ng\\) guitar styles and songs that trace their roots to the paniolos \\(Ha
 waiian cowboys\\)\, along with delightful stories of Hawai‘i and their l
 ives in music.\n\n=====\n\nHora del espectáculo: 7:00 p. m.\n\nMaestros d
 e la Música Hawaiana presenta a tres de los músicos más populares del f
 amoso "Slack Key Show" de Maui: George Kahumoku Jr.\, cuatro veces ganador
  del Grammy y maestro de la guitarra slack key\; Led Kaapana\, miembro del
  Patrimonio Nacional\, cuyo estilo de punteo con la guitarra slack key es 
 inigualable\; y Sonny Lim\, quien toca tanto el lap steel \\(inventado en 
 Hawái\\) como la guitarra slack key. Juntos comparten los singulares esti
 los de guitarra slack key \\(afinación abierta\\) de Hawái y canciones c
 on raíces en los paniolos \\(vaqueros hawaianos\\)\, además de encantado
 ras historias de Hawái y su vida musical.
LOCATION:Brannan Center
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107556281?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ezra Lipp & Ray White & Steve Adams & Vicki Randle
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260311T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260311T000000
UID:2602249A7h-m7GcUamxSKTS5qN6A
DESCRIPTION:Ezra Lipp is an innovative\, Bay Area based drummer\, composer
  and educator\, who regularly performs with a slew of all star musicians\,
  works as an in demand session musician\, has his own teaching practice\, 
 leads his own band Magic In The Other\, and is the proud creator and host 
 of a music podcast called The Ezra Lipp Hour \\(More or Less\\) . He has e
 xtensively toured the US and Europe and has worked with many amazing bands
  and artists representing diverse musical genres including Phil Lesh of th
 e Grateful Dead\, Melvin Seals and JGB\, counter-cultural Iranian supersta
 r Mohsen Namjoo\, national folk-soul treasure Sean Hayes and many\, many m
 ore \\[see below for a more complete list\\].\n\nEzra is a lifelong studen
 t of music and earned a bachelor’s degree in Music Performance and Jazz 
 studies from the University of Vermont in 2005. He has also studied music 
 and percussion from around the globe both in the US and abroad \\(includin
 g West African\, North Indian\, Afro-Cuban\, and more\\). As a teacher he 
 brings his depth and breadth of rhythmic knowledge and years of profession
 al experience to help others along on a path to find their own creative mu
 sical voice and expression.\n\nEzra’s imaginative approach\, accomplishe
 d musicianship and refined sensibilities distinguish him as a truly creati
 ve contemporary musician and drum artist.\n\n"Ezra Lipp appears and sounds
  utterly natural\, as if each of these varied environments is his organic 
 state as a drummer. He exhibits a steely-eyed\, no-holding-back intensity 
 that speaks of an artist that truly gives himself to the moment\, open ear
 s craning to catch what the music needs as his body blurs beautifully to t
 ease out the right moves and deliver them right on time. Our gut says Lipp
  is going to be one of the greats one day\, and it’s not going to suck t
 o witness his evolution along the way." - Dennis Cook\, Jambase/Dirty Impo
 und
LOCATION:HopMonk Tavern Novato
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/1037608036?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=2
 87&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: Celebrating Women
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260311T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260311T180000
UID:26021744m4_ruWfUGLa_u2Bh7bfQ
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  2/13/26\n\n**MARCH EXHIBIT: CELE
 BRATING WOMEN**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  February 23 – March 29\, 2026\n\n**R
 ECEPTION: SATURDAY\, MARCH 7\, 2026\, 4-6 pm: Join in to meet the artists 
 and celebrate the show. Take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing 
 for a beautiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**
 \n\nSonoma County artist\, **Tosya Shore\,** presents **Celebrating Women\
 ,** paintings that commemorate women in honor of Women’s History Month. 
 Shore’s watercolor works capture women in their element\, showing the mu
 ltiple facets of their lives.  These dynamic paintings break away with st
 rong shapes and interlacing patterns that draw the viewer in exciting ways
 .  A la Degas\, we catch a ballet dancer lacing her shoes in “Good Poin
 t.”  The artist takes us into nature with “Redwood Rendezvous” wher
 e dominant trunk shapes frame a couple enjoying a glorious forest scene. 
    “Just Back from Vegas” captures a fleeting view of elegance as th
 e woman in question catches her breath.  “There’s such special feelin
 g in these everyday moments\, I love to turn the mundane into magic – wo
 men deserve nothing less\,” noted Shore. \n\nMeet the artist: Shore wil
 l be hosting the Gallery on March 5 and 19 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\n The Sta
 irway Smallworks Showcase features **Donna Schaffer’s Ooh La La\, Plein 
 Air\,** a collection unveiling oil paintings made on her recent trip to Fr
 ance.  Roaming the streets of Paris\, toting paints and palette\, Schaffe
 r captured iconic scenes buzzing with “la belle vie.” The viewer catch
 es a true cultural vibe in “Café le Bistro”\, the site of a favored h
 angout for espresso and conversation.  One is awed by the structure risin
 g from the ground-level trees in Schaffer’s unique view of the Eiffel To
 wer in “Paris is for Lovers.” “Every day was an adventure in Paris 
 – I hope through these plein air vignettes\, to share the excitement of 
 being there”\, stated Schaffer.\n\nMeet the artist: Schaffer will be hos
 ting the Gallery on March 21 and 22 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nUpstairs Art Gal
 lery\, 306 Center Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DA
 ILY: 11am – 6 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further 
 information: Contact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net o
 r 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
