BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Rent School Edition"- Musical
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T220000
UID:260305bWXQ8AGkcEeSwuHOFyNLpQ
DESCRIPTION:Set in the East Village of New York City\, Rent School Edition
  is about falling in love\, finding your voice and living for today. Winne
 r of the Tony Award for Best Musical and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama\, it
  has become a pop cultural phenomenon with songs that rock and a story tha
 t resonates with audiences of all ages.\n\nBased loosely on Puccini’s La
  Boheme\, Rent School Edition follows a year in the life of a group of imp
 overished young artists and musicians struggling to survive and create in 
 New York’s Lower East Side\, under the shadow of HIV/AIDS. The physical 
 and emotional complications of the disease pervade the lives of Roger\, Mi
 mi\, Tom and Angel. Maureen deals with her chronic infidelity through perf
 ormance art\; her partner\, Joanne\, wonders if their relationship is wort
 h the trouble. Benny has sold out his Bohemian ideals in exchange for a he
 fty income and is on the outs with his former friends. Mark\, an aspiring 
 filmmaker\, feels like an outsider to life in general. How these young boh
 emians negotiate their dreams\, loves and conflicts provides the narrative
  thread to this groundbreaking musical.\n\nCredits\n\nBook\, Music\, and L
 yrics by Jonathan Larson\n\nDirected by Kele Gasparini\n\nEnjoy our LIVE P
 it Orchestra\n\nTickets: GoFan.CO \n\nhttps://gofan.co/app/school/CA23048
 \n\nSuggested Audience Age 13\\+\n\nContent Warnings\n\nAdult Themes\, Dri
 nking\, Drugs & Smoking\, Mild Language
LOCATION:San Marin High - Emily Gates Performing Arts Center
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/rent-school-edition-mus
 ical/18179688/2026-03-12T19
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bottle Baby Breakfast Club
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T160000
UID:260305aDvIZCAj-0-Qh6UwFUFUIA
DESCRIPTION:**Tiny Hooves\, Big Hearts: Our Ongoing Rescue Mission**\n\n**
 At Goatlandia\, our mission is simple: to give love\, safety\, and a secon
 d chance to animals who need it most.**\n\n**We were recently called to re
 scue three baby goats. These tiny babies are now safe at Goatlandia\, and 
 they need bottle feeding several times a day to stay healthy and thrive.**
 \n\n**That’s Where You Come In: The Bottle Baby Breakfast Club**\n\n**St
 arting March 6th\, join us for a heartwarming hour on the farm\, bottle-fe
 eding and cuddling our newest rescues while supporting their care.**\n\n**
 Your $250 donation (covers milk and supplies for weeks of feedings) includ
 es admission for up to four guests for a private\, unforgettable visit to 
 Goatlandia.**\n\n**Come share the love\, feel the magic\, and help us give
  these little ones the future they deserve.**
LOCATION:Goatlandia
URL:https://www.goatlandia.org/bottle-babies-breakfast-club
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Garcia Project
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T200000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T000000
UID:260227XXaeGUItgUyZ8MmmC74zOg
DESCRIPTION:We’re thrilled to welcome Jacklyn LaBranch to join The Garci
 a Project for our two-night run at The Mystic Theatre in Petaluma\, CA on 
 March 12 & 13\, 2026.\n\nJackie is beloved by fans around the world for he
 r role as a vocalist with the classic Jerry Garcia Band from 1982–1995\,
  where her soulful harmonies and unmistakable presence became an essential
  part of the sound of those late-era tours. Having her with us makes this 
 run especially meaningful.\n\nThese shows will recreate a special consecut
 ive two-night run from the classic Jerry Garcia Band late-’80s to ’90s
  era\, performed in full and in order — bringing audiences back to the f
 eel\, flow\, pacing\, and spirit of those unforgettable nights.\n\n“They
  remind me of what it felt like to sing these beautiful songs with Jerry G
 arcia.”\n\n— Jacklyn LaBranch\, Singer for The Jerry Garcia Band 1982
 –1995\n\nTickets on sale Friday Dec 12 at 10 am PST:\n\n• NIGHT 1: bit
 .ly/TGP-Mystic-Night1-3-12-26\n\n• NIGHT 2: bit.ly/TGP-Mystic-Night2-3-1
 3-26\n\nTwo Nights of Late-Era Jerry Garcia Band — Performed Live\, Star
 t to Finish�March 12 & 13 • Mystic Theatre • Petaluma\, CA\n\nExperi
 ence a consecutive-night run celebrating the powerful late-’80s through 
 ’90s eras of the classic Jerry Garcia Band. The Garcia Project will recr
 eate complete\, unaltered setlists from this period — different setlists
  each night — capturing the deep grooves\, soaring ballads\, and spiritu
 al energy from Jerry’s later years.\n\nFans often describe The Garcia Pr
 oject as the “DSO of the classic Jerry Garcia Band\,” and these shows 
 highlight why: every arrangement\, tone\, vocal feel\, and transition is p
 erformed with precision and heart.\n\nWhether you join us for one night or
  the full run\, expect two nights of rare late-era magic — just as it we
 nt down.\n\n------------\n\nThe Garcia Project performs full\, unaltered c
 lassic Jerry Garcia Band setlists from 1976–1995 — song for song\, set
  for set — using era-correct arrangements\, tempos\, instrumentation\, a
 nd gear to recreate the authentic sound that defined those legendary shows
 .\n\nThe Garcia Project is more than a tribute\, the band delivers the emo
 tional and communal experience that made the classic Jerry Garcia Band so 
 beloved. A recent Grateful Web feature described their performances as “
 a night of healing\, heart\, and pure Jerry magic\,” noting that The Gar
 cia Project opens “a little doorway back to the Jerry Garcia Band years\
 ,” with the same warmth\, looseness\, and deep musical breath that defin
 ed the original concerts.\n\nOver the years\, fans have affectionately dub
 bed The Garcia Project the ‘DSO of JGB’ — not as a comparison to any
  other band\, but to express the level of precision\, intention\, and resp
 ect they bring to recreating classic shows.\n\nTheir authenticity has earn
 ed praise from the musicians who lived it:\n\n“They remind me of what it
  felt like to sing these beautiful songs with Jerry Garcia.”�— Jackl
 yn LaBranch\, Singer for The Jerry Garcia Band 1982–1995\n\n“They are 
 Jerry’s kindred spirits when it comes to making music.”�— Buzz Buc
 hanan\, Drummer for The Jerry Garcia Band 1977–1978\n\n“…they almost
  make me feel like I’m back in\, say\, 1992 at the Warfield.”�— De
 nnis McNally\, former publicist for the Jerry Garcia Band and The Grateful
  Dead\n\n“They don't merely recreate Jerry’s music… they are channel
 ing it.”�— Maria Muldaur\, Grammy-nominated vocalist\, toured with T
 he Jerry Garcia Band 1977–79\n\n“The Garcia Project scratches that itc
 h for hearing live renditions of Jerry Garcia Band shows…”�— Bob M
 inkin\, iconic rock photographer\n\n“These players really get the soul o
 f the classic Jerry Garcia Band…”�— Andy Logan\, Grateful Guitars 
 Foundation\n\nWhether you experienced those classic shows decades ago or n
 ever had the chance\, The Garcia Project offers a powerful\, faithful\, an
 d deeply felt concert experience that keeps the spirit and magic of the cl
 assic Jerry Garcia Band alive.\n\nThe Garcia Project is proud to partner w
 ith DR Strings for our upcoming West Coast tour. Known for their handcraft
 ed\, high-quality strings made in the USA\, DR Strings brings unmatched to
 ne\, consistency\, and feel to every performance.   Check our DR Strin
 gs Here: https://bit.ly/DRStrings-TGP-2026
LOCATION:Mystic Theatre & Music Hall
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107705768?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"You're My Neighbor" Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T090000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T180000
UID:2602278pXoivM3FEm4KQU4i6cJ1g
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
