BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Opening Reception: Americana Reimagined and States of Anxiety\, St
 ates of Hope works by Inez Storer
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T173000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260312T193000
UID:260307SM_xSlIWDEy-X8COJXsmpQ
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the opening reception of PAC's Americana Reimagine
 d exhibition and Inez Storer's States of Anxiety\, States of Hope: Thursda
 y\, March 12\, 5:30-7:30pmAdmission is Free but space is limited so reserv
 e your ticket/s now before it is sold out.\n\nAbout Americana Reimagined: 
 On the 250th anniversary of the founding of the United States\, Americana 
 Reimagined invited artists from across the greater Bay Area to explore\, r
 einterpret\, and reimagine the visual language of &ldquo\;Americana&rdquo\
 ;. This juried exhibition looks beyond nostalgia to examine how familiar s
 ymbols\, stories\, and styles evolve over time&mdash\;bridging the past an
 d present through creativity and craft. \n\n&ldquo\;Americana&rdquo\; has 
 long served as a reflection of everyday life and culture\, from small-town
  iconography and handmade crafts to design movements and popular imagery. 
 In Americana Reimagined artists reexamine this broad theme\, juxtaposing t
 he old and the new\, and honoring timeless motifs while offering fresh per
 spectives on what they mean today.\n\nJurors \n\nDonna Seager\, Donna Seag
 er Fine Arts &amp\; Artists' Books  Richard Neill\, Multimedia Artist and 
 Film curator Simon Corwin\, Petaluma Artist and Jewelry\n\nStates of Anxie
 ty\, States of HopeExhibition Dates: March 12 - April 18\, 2026Opening Rec
 eption: Thursday\, March 12\, 5:30-7:30pm\n\nAbout States of Anxiety\, Sta
 tes of Hope: This exhibition presents a selection of works by artist Inez 
 Storer that reflect on the emotional\, cultural\, and political complexiti
 es of contemporary life. Building on themes explored in Americana Reimagin
 ed\, Storer's paintings offer a layered meditation on identity\, memory\, 
 and collective experience in times of uncertainty and transformation.\n\nT
 hrough her distinctive magical realist collage method\, Storer constructs 
 richly textured visual narratives that merge personal history with broader
  social realities. Her works are composed of fragments&mdash\;symbols\, im
 ages\, and artifacts drawn from her life and interests.\n\nStorer's painti
 ngs guide the viewer on a journey through both historical memory and inter
 nal landscapes. They balance darkness and light\, anxiety and hope.  She a
 sks us to reflect on the conditions of our moment. States of Anxiety\, Sta
 tes of Hope affirms art's capacity to illuminate struggle while nurturing 
 resilience\, empathy\, and connection.
LOCATION:Petaluma Arts Center
URL:https://mynorthbaytickets.ticketsauce.com/e/opening-reception-american
 a-states-of-anxiety?aff=cityspark
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
