BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Online: Resilience & the Open Heart: Somatic Practices for Everyda
 y Stress
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T183000
UID:260213RE3iSVDxnUWV4pzQzbRXsw
DESCRIPTION:**with Pawan Bareja\, PhD**\n\nWhen we are out of alignment wi
 th our deepest heart values\, life feels stressful. Whether the trigger is
  personal heartbreak\, economic pressure\, relational conflict\, or the we
 ight of the climate crisis\, the body often reacts with anxiety\, collapse
 \, anger\, or overwhelm long before the mind can make sense of it. You are
  invited to move from stress to love by transforming these patterns throug
 h embodied heart practices.\n\nEach week\, we will begin by gently noticin
 g where activation lives in the body. We’ll then engage in embodied hea
 rt-opening practices to soothe the nervous system and reconnect with inner
  clarity. After practice\, we will re-check the nervous system to observe 
 what has shifted\, revealing resilience as something softly felt\, measura
 ble\, and trainable.\n\nAs the heart opens and the body softens\, many exp
 erience deeper rest\, clearer thinking\, a renewed sense of connection to 
 loved ones\, and the courage to live a more meaningful life.
LOCATION:Spirit Rock Meditation Center
URL:https://courses.spiritrock.org/sp/resilience-and-the-open-heart-somati
 c-practices-for-everyday-stress/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
