UID:260303WT6Kek6IWEiWk1WvqV-HrA
DESCRIPTION:Drop in and sing and make friends. Guided by David Worm in thi
 s 2-part offering to deepen in the art of making improvised music with the
  support of community.\n\nContinuing how a bass and rhythm section can tra
 nsform your melody. We'll deepen our practice and explore song form this t
 ime\, and of course there's always room to just play. There will be lots o
 f singing together\, interspersed with individualized "workshopping" with 
 David\, as the moment calls. Open to any experience/comfort level with sin
 ging and/or improvised singing. \n\nRequested Contribution:\n\n$20-30 eit
 her morning or afternoon\, or $40-$50 for both sessions (cash\, Venmo or P
 aypal) paid upon arrival. No one turned away for financial reasons. First 
 session is 10:30 am - noon\, second session is 12:30-2:00 pm. \n\nWe'll h
 ave a half-hour break partway through - good for snacking\, lunch\, walkin
 g\, talking\, fresh air\, etc. Please bring a cannister with water for you
 rself\, and a sack lunch.
