DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T130000
UID:2602124g29umeXNEiCTKrlddU2Jg
DESCRIPTION:Do you have a lamp\, small appliance\, textile\, or bike in ne
 ed of repair?\n\nBring it to the Repair Fair!\n\nVolunteers and specialize
 d repair professionals will be on-hand to repair\\* your items.  We ask 
 that you stay with your item while it's being fixed\, so you can learn tip
 s for future maintenance\, how to shop for repairable goods\, and even how
  to repair things yourself!  \n\nIf you’d like to bring an item to r
 epair\, please register the item here: https://www.reusealliance.org/rf-re
 g \\(Pre-registering allows us to prepare for your item!\\)\n\nThis is a f
 ree public event.\n\nThis event will also include a Clothing Swap. Please 
 bring clothing items and accessories \\(clean and in good shape\\) to shar
 e and bring home something new to you!\n\n\\*We cannot guarantee your item
 \\(s\\) will be repaired\, depending on the existing damage or breakage\, 
 ability of volunteer fixers\, and availability of materials for repair. No
 te we cannot work on microwaves and we can’t repair cell phones but we
 ’re happy to refer you to local professionals who can. In addition\, the
  textile department is not able to perform the following:\n\nReplacing zip
 pers\n\nRepairing shoes\, leather\, or vinyl materials\n\nPerforming alter
 ations \\(making garments bigger/smaller\\)\n\nReplacing rivets/grommets\n
 \nHemming certain fabrics \\(stretchy fabric\, sleek/luxury fabrics e.g. p
 rom dresses\\)\n\nIf you are in need of garment hemming\, we require that 
 you please pin your garment to the desired length before you arrive.\n\nJo
 in Us!\n\nDoes fixing things sound like a fun way to spend a Saturday afte
 rnoon?  Or want to help out in other ways?  We need you!\n\nEmail volunt
 eer@reusealliance.org or sign up here: https://volunteersignup.org/RMHLA
LOCATION:San Geronimo Valley Community Center
URL:https://www.reusealliance.org/events/san-geronimo-repair-fair
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
