BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hanging with Horses: Middle School
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T103000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T120000
UID:260305f7HVnowXekm1Omhyr8fpdQ
DESCRIPTION:Middle school can be… a lot. Friendships changing. Siblings.
  Academic stress. Anxious moments. Parents. You know. Horses are amazing f
 riends\, guides\, listeners\, and healers. They really know about relation
 ships. AND they are experts at stress management. Hanging with Horses: Mid
 dle School is a three-week group meeting consecutively on Sundays\, March 
 15-29\, 10:30 AM\, on a beautiful old cattle ranch between Novato and Peta
 luma. If you join **Hanging with Horses**\, you will have a blast and beco
 me a part of a wonderful herd (horses and humans.) You might also...\n\nTr
 y grounding and relaxation tools that actually help.\n\nBuild confidence a
 nd leadership—just by being yourself.\n\nLearn to speak horse while cari
 ng for the herd.\n\nYou don’t have to talk if you’re not ready. You do
 n’t have to be “good with people.” You don’t need any horse experi
 ence.\n\nJust come as you are. The horses will meet you there 🐎✨\n\nT
 hrough unpressured time “hanging with horses\,” guided group conversat
 ions\, and hands-on experiences\, participants will learn to:\n\nUnderstan
 d what stress and anxiety feel like in their own bodies\n\nBuild healthier
  friendships and boundaries\n\nDevelop emotional awareness and leadership 
 skills\n\nPractice grounding and calming tools they can use anywhere\n\nGa
 in confidence by tuning into themselves and their environment\n\nHorses na
 turally reflect emotions and stress levels\, giving kids a powerful (and n
 on-judgmental) way to learn about themselves and others.\n\n🐎**NEIGH**:
  You can schedule a call to speak with the director of Heart & Mind Equine
  to learn more and see if this group is a good option for your family. Sch
 edule here.\n\nScholarships are available. Please reach out or schedule a 
 call to request- HeartMindEquine@gmail.com\n\nLearn more and register here
 : https://hwhorses-middle-school.eventbrite.com
LOCATION:Heart & Mind Equine Horse Rescue
URL:https://hwhorses-middle-school.eventbrite.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Rent School Edition"- Musical
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T170000
UID:260305cZqMu62FHU6MKs-5IXIfEw
DESCRIPTION:Set in the East Village of New York City\, Rent School Edition
  is about falling in love\, finding your voice and living for today. Winne
 r of the Tony Award for Best Musical and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama\, it
  has become a pop cultural phenomenon with songs that rock and a story tha
 t resonates with audiences of all ages.\n\nBased loosely on Puccini’s La
  Boheme\, Rent School Edition follows a year in the life of a group of imp
 overished young artists and musicians struggling to survive and create in 
 New York’s Lower East Side\, under the shadow of HIV/AIDS. The physical 
 and emotional complications of the disease pervade the lives of Roger\, Mi
 mi\, Tom and Angel. Maureen deals with her chronic infidelity through perf
 ormance art\; her partner\, Joanne\, wonders if their relationship is wort
 h the trouble. Benny has sold out his Bohemian ideals in exchange for a he
 fty income and is on the outs with his former friends. Mark\, an aspiring 
 filmmaker\, feels like an outsider to life in general. How these young boh
 emians negotiate their dreams\, loves and conflicts provides the narrative
  thread to this groundbreaking musical.\n\nCredits\n\nBook\, Music\, and L
 yrics by Jonathan Larson\n\nDirected by Kele Gasparini\n\nEnjoy our LIVE P
 it Orchestra\n\nTickets: GoFan.CO \n\nhttps://gofan.co/app/school/CA23048
 \n\nSuggested Audience Age 13\\+\n\nContent Warnings\n\nAdult Themes\, Dri
 nking\, Drugs & Smoking\, Mild Language
LOCATION:San Marin High - Emily Gates Performing Arts Center
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/rent-school-edition-mus
 ical/18179688/2026-03-15T14
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
