BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Glass Menagerie
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T160000
UID:260227f36TvpQv50yxviLzkhNUBA
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Season at Curtain Call Theatre starts off with **The 
 Glass Menagerie**\, the play that made Tennessee Williams famous.\n\nHave 
 You Ever Felt Stuck Between Your Dreams and Reality? This Play Gets It.\n\
 nImagine being trapped in a tiny apartment during the Great Depression —
  no money\, no way out\, just a family clinging to hopes that may never co
 me true. That's exactly what The Glass Menagerie is about.\n\nWritten by T
 ennessee Williams — one of America's greatest playwrights — this story
  follows a restless son\, an overbearing mom\, and a painfully shy daughte
 r as they each chase dreams that feel just out of reach. It's emotional\, 
 poetic\, and honestly… kind of hits different when you think about your 
 own life.\n\nThis iconic play is literally studied in classrooms worldwide
 \, so seeing it live is like watching your textbook come to life — excep
 t way more powerful.\n\n📅 March 13–29\, 2026\n\n📍 20347 Hwy 116\, 
 Monte Rio\, CA\n\n🎟️ Grab your tickets at russianriverhall.com or cal
 l (707) 387-5072\n\nThe Glass Menagerie by Tennessee Williams is directed 
 by Michael Tabib.\n\nShowing at the Russian River Hall in Monte Rio\, CA f
 rom March 13-29\, 2026.\n\nProgram was made possible\, in part\, with fund
 s from Creative Sonoma and the California Arts Council (CAC).\n\nBy specia
 l arrangement with Dramatists Play Services\, Inc.
LOCATION:Curtain Call Theatre
URL:https://www.russianriverhall.com/2026/02/18/march-13-29-the-glass-mena
 gerie/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"You're My Neighbor" Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T170000
UID:260227ZEiHVtcn6EGGNe7BZsYsxg
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sunday Sessions with "Fire Up!"
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T130000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T180000
UID:260227QDw6sh1hQE2FCW8926AxHA
DESCRIPTION:Griffo is excited to welcome Fire Up!\, a Bay Area Tribute to 
 the Garcia Saunders Songbook. This rotating cast of players will have you 
 transported with the first tune. Bodega Market Deli will be serving up foo
 d all day while the Griffo crew serves up delicious cocktails from our eve
 r rotating menu! Don't miss this homage to an era of music that never goes
  out of style!\n\nSee you Sundays!\n\nWho's Playing: Fire Up!\n\nWho's Coo
 king: Bodega Market Deli\n\nWhen: Sunday\, March 15th - Doors @ 1 pm\n\nWh
 ere: Griffo Distillery\n\nPlease RSVP for this FREE\, All Ages Event. Spac
 e is Limited.\n\nAbout the Band:\n\nFire up! Is a tribute band interpretin
 g the Jerry Garcia “Legion of Mary” era. Fire Up! is branded as “Son
 gs from the Garcia – Saunders songbook."\n\nFor note\, Fire Up! is a nam
 e of a Garcia Saunders studio album\, https://open.spotify.com/album/2b85g
 bWiMbAg3cvSUTMIBp\n\nOur project is funky\, bluesy\, Jamy\, RnB\, and Jazz
 y with an emphasis on the Hammond organ. One might say “Ballroom brawlin
 g\, baby making music" modeled after the 1972 – 1975 Legion of Mary era.
  It is different than what you hear from other JGB bands who focus on more
  of the 80’s and 90’s gospel Jerry era.
LOCATION:Griffo Distillery
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1469435291544648/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Look\, Listen and Bird!
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T113000
UID:260226V3SpfdyEfEKnW3vcCH_MRQ
DESCRIPTION:We will focus (pun intended) on learning stories and 
 field characteristics of local and migrating birds in the variety
  of Sugarloaf habitats\, with an emphasis on ear birding. We’l
 l discuss identification\, migration\, adaptations and our importan
 t role in improving habitat for birds. Let’s try to observe a
 t least 20 species!\n\nMeet at the White Barn parking lot. Ticke
 ts are $10 for general admission\, $5 for youth (12-17 year old
 s\; all minors must be accompanied by a parent or legal guardia
 n)\, students\, Sugarloaf members\, Sugarloaf or RFO volunteers\, 
 and free for children under 12. Wear layers\, appropriate footwea
 r for muddy and/or slippery trails\, bring at least a quart of
  water\, sun protection\, and if desired\, a snack. Binoculars a
 re optional but welcome. Rain cancels. Parking fees apply.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/looklistenbird
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonoma Mushroom Foraging
