DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T140000
UID:260226AqK7iR7cPUq73O7QnNVoUw
DESCRIPTION:These guided mushroom walks are about 2.5 hours north of San F
 rancisco in Sonoma.  All details you need\, including packing list\, meet
 -up location\, and more will be sent once your booking is confirmed.  Thi
 s is a wonderful weekend adventure to do alone or with friends and family.
  \n\nWhat You'll Learn\n\nThis experiential\, hands-on half-day program i
 s all about the fascinating world of fungi and begins at 10:00 am. Learni
 ng to forage for mushrooms is an ongoing life path. This program will teac
 h you foundational skills to be able to go out foraging on your own. We w
 ill cover mushroom anatomy for identification\, symbiotic tree and plant r
 elationships\, poisonous and edible mushrooms\, and forest safety.  This 
 winter\, it will be possible to find edibles such as porcini\, chanterelle
 \, yellowfoot\, black trumpet\, hedgehog\, and more.  The program also in
 cludes community building\, mindful movement\, a cooking demo\, and a tast
 ing at the end.
LOCATION:Sonoma Coast
URL:https://www.forkinthepath.org/schedule/mushroom-foraging-sonoma-2025-l
 c6g9-shkzj-99aa8
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Group Healing Circles Ceremony/Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T150000
UID:260225_gIqQYaVZUaRbthreKNhvQ
DESCRIPTION:This is an experiential intimate workshop arranged in two circ
 les of 7 participants\, designed to promote individual and group healing o
 n physical\, mental\, emotional and spiritual levels.\n\nIt is a guided in
 teractive process\, in which each participant will experience a variety of
  techniques using light\, sound\, touch\, energy and ancient wisdom healin
 g techniques. The goal of this ceremony is to help each person come into a
  place of inner balance and alignment. Circles and groups will be changed 
 approximately every 30-40 minutes allowing those in the center and the out
 er circles to receive the Gift of Creation.\n\n“The concept of simultane
 ous wheels of group healing was awesome to observe and participate with. 
  To observe Dr. Maria float from one circle to another identifying specifi
 c notes/frequencies given to her by Spirits for each specific person was a
 mazing. She also instructed people to aim certain colors to certain organs
 \, to allow for deeper healing to happen. The releases\, relief and raisin
 g of individual vibrations was absolutely amazing.”\n\nWhat makes this e
 vent especially powerful is that it takes place within the amplified bioen
 ergetic field of the EESystem. As Dr. Maria speaks about cellular resonanc
 e\, coherence\, and restoring balance\, guests will simultaneously be imme
 rsed in a scalar-energy environment designed to support optimal cellular c
 ommunication and energetic harmony. Whether you are new to her work or alr
 eady familiar with energy-based healing\, this is an invitation to explore
  what becomes possible when wisdom\, frequency\, and intention align. We l
 ook forward to welcoming you into the field.\n\nAbout Dr Maria Michael\n\n
 Dr. Maria D. Michael is a world renowned and respected medical intuitive\,
  channel\, empath\, healer\, psychic and teacher for over 40 years. She ha
 s been awarded 5 advanced degrees \\(all Summa Cum Laude\\)\, including a 
 Ph.D. in Counseling Psychology. She has doctorate-level training in Neurop
 sychology and Special Education and extensive post-doctoral studies in Psy
 choanalysis and Jungian Psychology. Additionally\, Dr. Michael is trained 
 and experienced in EMDR\, Hypnotherapy\, LENS Neurofeedback\, Neurolinguis
 tic Programming\, Eriksonian Hypnosis Training. She is a Lakota/Diné \\(N
 avajo\\) Traditional elder\, has participated in and led traditional Nativ
 e ceremonies and doctored alongside Lakota Medicine people. She has been s
 ought out worldwide for her powerful Medicine Energies and Healing abiliti
 es. Learn more about Dr Maria Michael at: https://drmariamichael.com/\n\nB
 ELIEFS\n\nDr. Maria Michael believes that we all come from the same Creati
 on\, and that everyone has the potential and capacity to communicate with 
 Creation. While the Lakota call Creation “The Great Mystery\,” other t
 raditions may refer to Creation\, with names such as\, “God\,” “the 
 Universe\,” “Allah\,” “Yahweh\,” “Divine Love\,” “Universa
 l Love” or “Cosmic Consciousness.”\n\nWe not only choose our human f
 amilies\, but also we choose\, initially at least\, our own unique form or
  tradition of understanding and communication with the Great Mystery. No f
 orm or tradition is better than another. Humans are merely attempting to u
 nderstand “That” which is beyond comprehension.\n\nAll messages from t
 he Great Mystery are compassionate and loving\, even though at times these
  messages may appear difficult. Creation’s message appears to us in what
 ever way we choose to comprehend it. Sometimes\, we are only capable of co
 mprehending deeply sensitive messages that resound in our hearts\, and som
 etimes only strong and “seemingly” shocking messages penetrate our def
 enses. This loving Spirit guides us to remove those obstacles that stand i
 n our way of becoming all that Creation and We intended us to be.
LOCATION:Energy Wave Center
URL:https://energywavecenter.com/gift-of-creation/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:In Her Power
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T160000
UID:260225EKTcwerDGkmH5lJbWq2QtA
DESCRIPTION:In Her Power\n\nA Collaboration by Priscila Soares & JeanCheri
 e\n\nIn Her Power is a group exhibition celebrating women’s presence\, s
 trength\, and creative expression. Anchored by a collaborative\, life-size
  sculptural work by Priscila Soares and JeanCherie\, the exhibition brings
  together works by women artists exploring power as something lived\, embo
 died\, and deeply personal.\n\nAt the heart of the gallery stands a mounta
 in lioness woman — a guardian figure shaped by two artists working toget
 her\, each bringing her own voice\, materials\, and vision. Surrounding th
 is central work\, invited artists contribute pieces that reflect their own
  relationship to power\, resilience\, intuition\, and selfhood.\n\nRather 
 than offering a single definition\, In Her Power invites viewers to witnes
 s many expressions of strength — quiet and fierce\, ancestral and contem
 porary\, individual and shared. It is both a celebration of women artists 
 and an invitation to step into presence\, creativity\, and connection.\n\n
 Opening Reception:\n\nMarch 1\, 12–4pm\n\nGallery Hours:\n\nSundays in M
 arch\, 12–4pm\n\nLocation:\n\nMare Island Art Studios\n\n110 Pintado St.
 \n\nVallejo\, CA
LOCATION:Mare Island Art Studios
URL:https://mareislandartstudios.com/events/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
