BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:In Her Power Group Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T160000
UID:260223nqV5Yav1PUW4b7AW6Obgww
DESCRIPTION:In Her Power is a group exhibition celebrating women's presenc
 e\, strength\, and creative expression. Anchored by a collaborative\, life
 -size sculptural work by resident artists Priscila Soares and JeanCherie\,
  the exhibition brings together works by women artists exploring power as 
 something lived\, embodied\, and deeply personal. At the heart of the gall
 ery stands a mountain lioness woman - a guardian figure shaped by two arti
 sts working together\, each bringing her own voice\, materials\, and visio
 n. Surrounding this central work\, invited artists contribute pieces that 
 reflect their own relationship to power\, resilience\, intuition\, and sel
 fhood. Rather than offering a single definition\, In Her Power invites vie
 wers to witness many expressions of strength - quiet and fierce\, ancestra
 l and contemporary\, individual and shared. It is both a celebration of wo
 men artists and an invitation to step into presence\, creativity\, and con
 nection. Opening Reception: March 1\, 12-4pm Gallery Hours: Sundays in Mar
 ch\, 12-4pm  Event website
LOCATION:Mare Island Art Studios
URL:https://www.visitvallejo.com/events/upcoming-events/in-her-power-group
 -art-exhibit-mar-15
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Women's Circle For The Pisces New Moon
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T183000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T203000
UID:260223QLeWevynkUyAYlVlfvSWqA
DESCRIPTION:Each new moon\, we gather to connect\, reflect\, and set inten
 tions in good company. This gentle evening ritual has been nurturing our c
 ommunity through seasons of change\, offering a monthly pause to breathe\,
  share\, and draw strength from each other. Whether you're a seasoned moon
  tracker or just curious about weaving some magic into your everyday life\
 , our circle welcomes you. Bring your thoughts\, your truth\, and perhaps 
 a journal- we'll provide the tea\, comfort and understanding. No crystals 
 required and absolutely no experience needed\, just real women\, real conv
 ersations\, and the quiet power of coming together. Women's New Moon Circl
 e at The Exchange: Where every month begins with sisterhood. This event is
  lead by Vallejo's own Britt Sandkulla Sinclair of Golden Thread Alchemy. 
 Britt is a Certified Integral Coach specializing in life balance\, a death
  doula\, astrologer\, a mother of 3 boys\, a collaborative partner and a s
 teward of all things wild! Visit her website to learn more about this cele
 stial powerhouse \\(yes\, she absolutely is made of stars\\). Tickets: $15
  Get tickets
LOCATION:The Exchange
URL:https://www.visitvallejo.com/events/upcoming-events/womens-circle-for-
 the-pisces-new-moon
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
