BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Free Uber\, Lyft\, and Cab Rides by Wells Call Injury Lawyers
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T170000
UID:260225F-bdTEwjiEi_oY2OeAtBOw
DESCRIPTION:According to the Annual Report of California DUI Management I
 nformation System\, of the total number of crash fatalities in 2018\, 32.1
 % were alcohol-related in California. We are committed to helping our comm
 unity not be a part of this statistic.\n\nWe pride ourselves on making our
  community safer and giving back to our neighbors as much as we can. That 
 is why this holiday season\, if you decide to go out and celebrate\, we wi
 ll pay for your cab ride home to ensure that you make it home safely.\n\nW
 e’d like to introduce a new community initiative: Free Uber\, Lyft\, and
  Cab Ride Program to help reduce the number of drunk drivers on the road d
 uring the holidays. This holiday season\, if you decide to go and drink\, 
 please make the responsible choice to grab a ride home instead of getting 
 behind the wheel. We will reimburse you for your fare home\, so save that 
 receipt!\n\nRead more about our Holiday Ride-Share Program below for full 
 details. \n\nHow it Works:\n\nThe program is simple. If you have been dri
 nking – take an Uber\, Lyft\, or cab\, and you’ll get a reimbursement 
 from us!\n\nWe want you home safe this holiday season.\n\nQualifying 2025 
 Holidays:\n\nSuper Bowl Sunday\n\nSt. Patrick’s Day\n\nCinco de Mayo\n\n
 Independence Day\n\nLabor Day\n\nHalloween\n\nThanksgiving Eve & Day\n\nNe
 w Year’s Eve & Day\n\nDetails to the Program:\n\nRides must be in Solano
  County\n\nRides must be taken between 5 pm on the day of the holiday and 
 10 am the next morning.\n\nYou must be of legal drinking age to qualify \\
 (21 and over\\).\n\nValid for one\, one-way ride to a safe destination.\n\
 nLimit one reimbursement per household.\n\nA maximum value of $25.00 anywh
 ere within Solano County.\n\nThe maximum value includes a tip of up to 10%
 . Anything above a 10% tip on the base fare will not be reimbursed.\n\nPar
 ticipation in this promotion is limited to the first 25 submissions.\n\nW
 hen Will I Get My Reimbursement?\n\nWithin 10 business days\, you must sub
 mit a copy of your receipt and photo ID via mail to our office. We will ma
 il you a check for your reimbursement of a qualifying submission within 30
  days of the holiday.\n\nWells Call Injury Lawyers 1455 Oliver Rd \\#110 F
 airfield\, CA 94534 707-273-1278 www.wccbc.com\n\nSubmissions are limited 
 and will fill up fast\, so don’t delay submitting your reimbursement.
LOCATION:CA 94534
URL:https://www.wccbc.com/free-ride-share/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
