SUMMARY:Sweet and Savory Tamales: Traditional Techniques
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T200000
UID:260207osgt4Q-8N0WwMkytA9P0Zg
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nWednesday\, March 18\, 2026 5:00 PM – 8:00 PM\n\
 nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nBilingual\, Culinary Arts\n\nAge\\(s\\)
 \n\n18 and older\n\n$100 – Registration CostMaster traditional tamal-mak
 ing with sweet and savory variations. Learn masa preparation\, filling tec
 hniques\, and steaming methods for authentic results.\n\nWhat you’ll do\
 n\nDive into the rich tradition of tamal-making in this comprehensive hand
 s-on class exploring both sweet and savory variations of this beloved Lati
 n American dish. Whether you’re new to tamales or looking to refine your
  technique\, you’ll gain confidence in every step of the process from pr
 eparing masa to achieving perfectly steamed results. Learn to work with ma
 sa dough\, understanding the proper texture and consistency that creates l
 ight\, tender tamales. You’ll prepare savory fillings that might include
  seasoned pork\, chicken with salsa verde\, cheese with peppers\, or black
  bean and vegetable options. Explore sweet variations featuring cinnamon\,
  fruit\, chocolate\, or traditional piloncillo for dessert-style tamales t
 hat are perfect for celebrations or breakfast. Master the art of spreading
  masa evenly on corn husks\, portioning fillings appropriately\, and foldi
 ng techniques that ensure your tamales hold together beautifully during st
 eaming. You’ll learn the secrets of proper steaming for consistent cooki
 ng and discover tips for making large batches ahead for freezing. Tamales 
 are central to celebrations and family gatherings across Latin America\, a
 nd this class honors that tradition while making the process approachable 
 for home cooks. Leave with recipes\, techniques\, and the skills to host y
 our own tamalada.Membership has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and
  above receive 10% off the registration cost for any class purchase over $
 40. Materials fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and find c
 ommunity\, connection\, and creativity.\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 109\, Rotary K
 itchen
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/sweet-and-savory-tamales/
