DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T193000
UID:260303rVRu1XPJvUav-XhLycOT4A
DESCRIPTION:Spanish explorers saw California as an Eden with abundant plan
 t and animal life because Native Californians intentionally and sustainabl
 y managed their environment in cooperation with nature for over 12\,000 ye
 ars. Join Duane BigEagle\, a Native American researcher from the College o
 f Marin\, to explore what we can we learn from this regenerative indigenou
 s environmental management model.
