BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Bonsai Show: Bonsai & Blossoms
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T170000
UID:260108TFyqPffqMUiyc29WKkS9Ow
DESCRIPTION:January 9–March 22\, 2026\n\nStep into a wonderland of bloom
 ing miniature trees to marvel at the living art of bonsai and the season
 ’s first flowers. Then stroll through our Asian Woodland to admire maje
 stic magnolias\, cherries\, and camellias in bloom\, or join a tour or pro
 gram to explore this timeless craft.\n\nThis year’s all-new presentation
  by the skilled artisans of the Redwood Empire Bonsai Society \\(REBS\\) h
 ighlights the grace and vitality of flowering bonsai—trees and shrubs tr
 ained to bloom in exquisite proportion to their diminutive scale. Delicate
  plum\, azalea\, camellia\, cherry\, and apricot bonsai take center stag
 e\, their blossoms appearing just as winter begins to yield to spring. The
 se early bloomers symbolize hope and renewal—reminding us that beauty an
 d resilience can emerge even in the coldest months.\n\nThe exhibition also
  draws inspiration from hanami\, the centuries-old Japanese tradition of 
 celebrating the fleeting beauty of blossoms. The Garden invites visitors t
 o participate in this art of flower appreciation through Hanami Strolls
 —guided walks through the Garden’s Asian woodland where early-blooming
  magnolias\, cherries\, and camellias offer their own ephemeral display.
LOCATION:Sonoma Botanical Garden
URL:https://sonomabg.org/visit/bonsai-and-blossoms/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Between the Lines Jr
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T160000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T190000
UID:251231RjIv77tXNEGAcEb_rmMzNA
DESCRIPTION:Join Spreckels Theatre Education Program this winter for our 8
  week teen production class of Between the Lines Jr\, for ages 13-17.\n\n
  An outsider in a new town and a new school\, Delilah seeks comfort in th
 e pages of her favorite book\, where she feels heard and understood by the
  handsome Prince Oliver. But as the lines between fantasy and reality begi
 n to blur in extraordinary ways\, Delilah realizes her dreams in the real
  world are worth fighting for.
LOCATION:Spreckels Center for the Performing Arts
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/between-the-lines-jr/17
 095188/2026-03-21T16
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Laguna Stewards at Colgan Creek/ Día de Laguna Stewards
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T090000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T120000
UID:2512067YZ1_tljqEuM3V4L2MEy8Q
DESCRIPTION:Come be a part of something special at Colgan Creek with the L
 aguna de Santa Rosa Foundation! Join us for a fun and rewarding day of han
 ds-on stewardship as we care for this creek. Starting at Taylor Mountain a
 nd flowing through Santa Rosa to Roseland and then to the Laguna de Santa 
 Rosa\, Colgan Creek has gone through many stages of restoration\, and we w
 ould like you to be a part of this new phase!\n\nThis is your chance to se
 e the creek’s incredible transformation and make a real impact in its on
 going care. Whether you're new to ecological restoration or an experienced
  volunteer\, everyone is welcome—of all ages and abilities. Let’s come
  together to nurture this beautiful creek and continue its journey toward 
 restoration. We can’t wait to share this experience with you!\n\nIMPORTA
 NT: Location details will be sent via email upon registration.\n\nPLEASE N
 OTE: All ages are welcome! No experience is necessary\; tools and training
  are provided.\n\nA big thank you to our Phase 3 project funders\, which i
 nclude the Department of Water Resources Urban Streams Restoration Program
 \, the Wildlife Conservation Board\, and the Sonoma County Agricultural Pr
 eservation and Open Space District. Additional Phase 3 partners include th
 e City of Santa Rosa and Rainforest Rising. We could not do this work with
 out them.\n\n¡Ven a formar parte de algo especial en el arroyo Colgan con
  la Laguna de Santa Rosa Foundation! Únete a nosotros para disfrutar de u
 n día divertido y gratificante de restauración mientras cuidamos de este
  arroyo. El arroyo Colgan\, que comienza en Taylor Mountain y fluye a trav
 és de Santa Rosa hasta Roseland y luego hasta la Laguna de Santa Rosa\, h
 a pasado por muchas etapas de restauración\, ¡y nos gustaría que fueras
  parte de esta nueva etapa!\n\nEsta es tu oportunidad de ver la increíble
  transformación del arroyo y generar un impacto real en su cuidado contin
 uo. Ya seas nuevo en la restauración ecológica o un voluntario experimen
 tado\, todos son bienvenidos\, de todas las edades y habilidades. Unámono
 s para cuidar este hermoso arroyo y continuar su viaje hacia la restauraci
 ón. ¡Estamos ansiosos por compartir esta experiencia contigo!\n\nLos det
 alles de la ubicación se enviarán por correo electrónico al registrarse
 .\n\nNOTA: ¡Son bienvenidas personas de todas las edades! No se necesita 
 experiencia\; se proporcionan herramientas y capacitación.\n\nAgradecemos
  enormemente a los financiadores de la Fase 3 del proyecto\, entre ellos e
 l Programa de Restauración de Arroyos Urbanos del Departamento de Recurso
 s Hídricos\, la Junta de Conservación de la Vida Silvestre y el Distrito
  de Preservación Agrícola y Espacios Abiertos del Condado de Sonoma. Otr
 os socios de la Fase 3 incluyen la Ciudad de Santa Rosa y Rainforest Risin
 g. ¡Sin ellos\, no podríamos realizar este trabajo!
LOCATION:Colgan Creek
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/laguna-stewards-at-colg
 an-creek-d-a-de-laguna-stewards/17585109/2026-03-21T09
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
