UID:2602241Ul-Z7rw_EupS65kd2PvLw
DESCRIPTION:Price: $56\, $45 \\(Marin Center Fees included\\)\n\nTicket In
 fo : https://tickets.marincenter.org/eventperformances.asp?evt=461\n\nPerf
 orming Arts Academy of Marin is delighted to present the beloved musical A
 nnie! With the book and score by Thomas Meehan\, Charle s Strouse\, and Ma
 rtin Charnin\, this Tony Award winning show brings fri endship\, adventure
 \, and family to the stage. Directed and choreographe d by PAAM's own Matt
 hew McCoy\, with featured choreography by CEO and Artistic Director Annie 
 Leese.\n\nJoin the big city adventure as the charming little orphan Annie 
 sets off to find her parents who left her at the orphanage run by the crue
 l and scheming Miss Hannigan. With help from her friends along the way\, A
 nnie finds a new home and discovers the true love of friendship and family
 . Our Mainstage Musical brings this beloved story to life and features the
  incredible talents of young actors as they transport you to 1930s New Yor
 k City.\n\nFeaturing performers ages 5 to 15\, along with the PAAM Dance S
 quad\, PAAM's Mainstage production is a part of our Theater Program\, whic
 h connect s the supportive community of peers that have a shared passion f
 or theater arts. PAAM's Theater Program offers students weekly musical the
 a ter training\, full-scale stage productions and performances\, private c
  oaching\, and workshops with industry professionals. We look forward to s
 eeing you in the studio and on stage!\n\nwww.paamarts.com
LOCATION:Showcase Theatre
URL:https://www.marincounty.gov/county-marin-calendar
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
