BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Family Stick Loom Weaving
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T153000
UID:260228r0SUuJvh-ESHZufEn_esdA
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, March 21\, 2026 2:00 – 3:30 PM\n\nLoc
 ation\n\nRoom 110\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nFamily\, Kids\n\nAg
 e\\(s\\)\n\n7-12\n\nAll children must be accompanied by an adult to attend
 .\n\n$30 – Per Family\, max of 3 people. Learn ancient stick loom weavin
 g in this hands-on class. Create a beautiful tapestry using natural materi
 als\, simple techniques\, and your choice of colors.\n\nAbout the Class\n\
 nCome learn the ancient craft of weaving with a stick loom! In this family
 -friendly class\, you’ll learn to hand-weave a simple tapestry using sti
 cks as your loom. The demonstration will include setting up the warp threa
 ds\, learning a simple over-under stitch pattern and the final knot step. 
 There will be a variety of stick shapes to choose from and plenty of room 
 to play with pattern and color. And voila! You’ll leave the class with y
 our stick-loom tapestry \\(either in progress or completed\, depending on 
 the chosen scale\\). Hang your weaving on your wall to bring nature indoor
 s or from a tree to bring your artistry outside! This class is open to par
 ents with their children ages 7 through 12.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/family-stick-loom-weaving/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Callie Watts
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T000000
UID:260227FNIMTYTj2k691HBuCCUCOw
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:Tasting Notes
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107935478?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:MovingWriting: Embodied Expressive Writing
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T170000
UID:260129fcPH01m7VE6-m4p9oF-VUw
DESCRIPTION:In MovingWriting workshops\, we play with movement/dance and
  words to help us connect with our deep and creative selves in the company
  of a supportive circle. Giving voice to our own stories and witnessing th
 e stories of others brings healing\, aliveness\, and connection with other
 s.\n\nNo moving or writing experience necessary!\n\nHere's what a few rece
 nt MovingWriting participants had to say about their experience:\n\n“L
 oretta's well-crafted writing prompts sparked a writer inside me that I di
 dn't know I had… I left feeling invigorated\, accomplished and proud of 
 myself for trying something new.”\n\n“I'm neither a writer nor a dance
 r\, but Loretta made it easy to put aside my inhibitions and let my emotio
 nal body lead the way… I recommend this class for anybody at all!”\n\n
 "It felt delicious to dive into my creative moving and language self with 
 others. For days after\, I felt both emptied and filled up creatively in w
 ays that I hadn’t felt in a long time."\n\n"I felt refreshed\, renewed\,
  and like I had processed some emotional blockages… The paths were opene
 d and the words just flowed."\n\nCome move and write with us! Visit www.Mo
 vingWriting.com to learn more & register for upcoming events.
LOCATION:A private studio in Sebastopol
URL:http://www.MovingWriting.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bachata Beginners Saturday
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T090000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T100000
UID:251213Z2jd-yvJckO_GTRk6jX3dw
DESCRIPTION:This class is perfect for bachata beginners that want to learn
  basic steps and skills\, or those who want to refresh their foundational 
 skills. We understand that learning something new can feel a little intimi
 dating. That’s why our supportive and relaxed environment is specificall
 y designed to make learning bachata basics an absolute blast!\n\nOur frien
 dly instructors will guide you through:\n\nBasic directional steps: You
 ’ll learn the fundamental movements that form the building blocks of all
  bachata dancing.\n\nProper frame for partner work: Discover how to conne
 ct comfortably and effectively with a partner\, setting you up for smooth 
 and enjoyable dances.\n\nSimple turn patterns: We’ll introduce you to e
 asy-to-follow turn patterns that will have you dancing with a partner in n
 o time.\n\nWe’ve carefully organized our curriculum to ensure that each 
 movement is easy to grasp and remember\, building your confidence with eve
 ry step. Our goal is to make learning fun. Join us to learn Bachata in Mar
 in.\n\nImportant Details\n\nNo dance experience required: Whether you’v
 e never danced before or it’s been a while\, you’re welcome here!\n\nN
 o partner necessary: Come solo or bring a friend—either way\, you’ll 
 have plenty of opportunities to dance.\n\nPlease wear non-marking shoe so
 les: This helps us keep our dance floor in great condition.\n\nCome join 
 us and discover the joy of bachata! We can’t wait to see you on the danc
 e floor.\n\nDate & Time:\n\nThursdays @ 6:30PM – 7:30PM Fridays @ 5:30PM
  – 6:30PM Saturdays @ 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM\n\nInstructor: Lucie Ebnerova
 \n\nAddress: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8 San Rafael\, CA\n\nNote: Arrive 10 
 minutes before. No floor marking shoe soles allowed.
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8 San Rafael
URL:https://salsadancemarin.com/bachata-beginners/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Salsa Beginner Marin – Saturday
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T110000
UID:251212IOAb0_bE1E2PGnSr-aOA9g
DESCRIPTION:**Ready to learn intermediate steps and technique?** Join on 
 on Saturday – Salsa Beginner Marin\n\nAre you a beginner who’s always 
 wanted to learn salsa? Salsa classes are designed to help you build a stro
 ng foundation. In this class\, you’ll learn the fundamental footwork\, p
 ractice the basic turns\, and understand the essential body movement that 
 will make you feel confident on the dance floor. This class is perfect for
  anyone ready to learn the techniques and foundational steps needed to sta
 rt their salsa journey.\n\nSalsa is fun\, and we make learning it stress-f
 ree! Our relaxed\, beginner-friendly class is the ideal starting point. Yo
 u don’t need a partner\, nor any dance experience!\n\nIn this class you 
 will learn:\n\nBasic directional steps that form the foundation of salsa.\
 n\nProper frame for comfortable and effective partner-work.\n\nSimple\, ea
 sy-to-remember turn patterns.\n\nGet ready to learn the fundamentals and h
 ave a great time!\n\n**Details:**\n\n**No partner necessary**—rotations 
 ensure everyone dances\n\nPlease wear **non-marking shoes** to protect t
 he floor\n\nArrive 10 minutes early\; warm up and settle in\n\n**When:** 
 Saturday\, 10:00 am – 11:00 am\n\n**Where:** 4140 Redwood Highway #8\, 
 San Rafael\, CA
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8\, San Rafael\, CA
URL:https://salsadancemarin.com/salsa-beginners-saturday/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
