DESCRIPTION:On Sunday\, March 22\, join us for a Last Supper–themed dinn
 er\, thoughtfully curated to bring together faith\, history\, fine wine\, 
 and community.\n\nThroughout the evening\, we will also reflect on the Las
 t Supper through a historical lens—exploring what this sacred meal meant
  to Jesus and His disciples in its original context\, and why its symbolis
 m of sacrifice\, covenant\, and shared table continues to resonate today. 
 Pastor Ted Max of Yountville Community Church will help guide this reflect
 ion.\n\nGuests will enjoy a four-course dinner with expertly paired Boisse
 t Collection wines. The evening is also inspired by Jean-Charles Boisset
 ’s book\, The Alchemy of the Senses\, which reflects on his vision of a 
 perfect Last Supper—one shared with inspiring individuals whose stories\
 , values\, and humanity enrich the table.\n\nThis gathering also celebrate
 s the shared vision of Yountville Community Church and its expansion to a 
 second campus in St. Helena\, furthering the restoration of historic churc
 hes and inclusive community spaces. A special thank you to Napa Valley res
 idents Celeste White and Robert White and Pastor Ted Max. Proceeds will be
 nefit the Salvation Army.\n\nBy Invitation Only Limited Tickets Available 
 Attire: Black Tie\n\n\\(Parking is very limited\, and car service is encou
 raged.\\)
