BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Flora & Fauna - Watercolor Course with Hannah Day at Bohemian Flow
 ers Farm
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T130000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T160000
UID:260225MXUTySs0M0erjIgyKaVfBQ
DESCRIPTION:In this 4 week course\, participants will learn a unique appro
 ach to watercolor\, intended to alleviate the frustration that many experi
 ence when learning this beautiful yet challenging medium. The class will f
 ocus on strengthening one's observational skills\, giving the artist a fou
 ndation off of which to build their paintings in a step by step layering p
 rocess\, that trains the artist to see value and color Our subject matter 
 will be flora and fauna - a sampling of plants and animals. These subjects
  are great for beginners and experienced artists alike\; their organic sha
 pes make them forgiving drawing subjects\, but their beauty can be a muse 
 for life. This class will work both from photographs and from life\, pract
 icing observational drawing in addition to watercolor technique. With 4 cl
 ass sessions\, participants will have the opportunity to develop their ski
 lls and build muscle memory with a medium that often feels like it has a m
 ind of its own. All materials provided. Location: Bohemian Flowers Farm\, 
 121 Bohemian Hwy\, Freestone\, CA Dates: Four Sundays - March 8\, 15\, 22\
 , 29 Time: 1 - 4 pm Ages: Adults Skill Levels: All Levels
LOCATION:D
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/flora-fauna-watercolor-course-with-ha
 nnah-day-at-bohemian-flowers-farm/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Performing Arts Academy of Marin Presents Annie the Musical!
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T130000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T150000
UID:260224mgFjomGR0Umci4T_5mKLMA
DESCRIPTION:Price: $56\, $45 \\(Marin Center Fees included\\)\n\nTicket In
 fo : https://tickets.marincenter.org/eventperformances.asp?evt=461\n\nPerf
 orming Arts Academy of Marin is delighted to present the beloved musical A
 nnie! With the book and score by Thomas Meehan\, Charle s Strouse\, and Ma
 rtin Charnin\, this Tony Award winning show brings fri endship\, adventure
 \, and family to the stage. Directed and choreographe d by PAAM's own Matt
 hew McCoy\, with featured choreography by CEO and Artistic Director Annie 
 Leese.\n\nJoin the big city adventure as the charming little orphan Annie 
 sets off to find her parents who left her at the orphanage run by the crue
 l and scheming Miss Hannigan. With help from her friends along the way\, A
 nnie finds a new home and discovers the true love of friendship and family
 . Our Mainstage Musical brings this beloved story to life and features the
  incredible talents of young actors as they transport you to 1930s New Yor
 k City.\n\nFeaturing performers ages 5 to 15\, along with the PAAM Dance S
 quad\, PAAM's Mainstage production is a part of our Theater Program\, whic
 h connect s the supportive community of peers that have a shared passion f
 or theater arts. PAAM's Theater Program offers students weekly musical the
 a ter training\, full-scale stage productions and performances\, private c
  oaching\, and workshops with industry professionals. We look forward to s
 eeing you in the studio and on stage!\n\nwww.paamarts.com
LOCATION:Showcase Theatre
URL:https://www.marincounty.gov/county-marin-calendar
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:In Her Power Group Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T160000
UID:260223CEqPA4BE8UGbqrnZfIX87w
DESCRIPTION:In Her Power is a group exhibition celebrating women's presenc
 e\, strength\, and creative expression. Anchored by a collaborative\, life
 -size sculptural work by resident artists Priscila Soares and JeanCherie\,
  the exhibition brings together works by women artists exploring power as 
 something lived\, embodied\, and deeply personal. At the heart of the gall
 ery stands a mountain lioness woman - a guardian figure shaped by two arti
 sts working together\, each bringing her own voice\, materials\, and visio
 n. Surrounding this central work\, invited artists contribute pieces that 
 reflect their own relationship to power\, resilience\, intuition\, and sel
 fhood. Rather than offering a single definition\, In Her Power invites vie
 wers to witness many expressions of strength - quiet and fierce\, ancestra
 l and contemporary\, individual and shared. It is both a celebration of wo
 men artists and an invitation to step into presence\, creativity\, and con
 nection. Opening Reception: March 1\, 12-4pm Gallery Hours: Sundays in Mar
 ch\, 12-4pm  Event website
LOCATION:Mare Island Art Studios
URL:https://www.visitvallejo.com/events/upcoming-events/in-her-power-group
 -art-exhibit-mar-22
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Signing + Meet & Greet with Karin Argoud
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T120000
UID:260218WgwVKUeuEUWtNDk04IMqHg
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special event with Karin Argoud\, author of Peti
 t Mouse Takes a Nap. This event is free! ABOUT THE BOOK For every book sol
 d\, author Karin Argoud will donate 5% net profit to the Save The Children
  Fund Sweet little Petite Mouse doesn’t want to nap \\(much like a child
  you probably know\\). With one tiny nose and two scurrying feet\, she’l
 l slip through your fingers! But with a little help from little hands\, yo
 u can make sure Petite Mouse gets some rest. With soft illustrations\, a f
 un counting element\, and finger holes for extra delight\, Petite Mouse Ta
 kes a Nap is the perfect naptime book to turn wiggly fingers into sleepy e
 yes. ABOUT THE AUTHOR Karin Argoud is an actress best known for her role a
 s Sonya Harper in the series Mama’s Family. She is also a freelance news
  journalist\, an author\, and the happily married mother of two daughters 
 who never really loved nap time. It was always quite the undertaking to ge
 t them to fall asleep. But she knew how important it was for them\, and wo
 uld sometimes go through stacks of books and songs to get them to fais dod
 o\, which means go to sleep in French. How she would have treasured a book
  like Petite Mouse Takes a Nap! She is a first-generation American and is 
 proud of her family's French American citizenship. Her loving\, wonderful 
 parents were of French\, German\, and Lebanese descent\, and she was raise
 d hearing fairy tales\, games\, and songs from those countries. She\, in t
 urn\, raised her daughters speaking French and immersed them in fairy tale
 s\, plays\, and songs. She and her husband sent their daughters to Waldorf
  schools and raised them without television\, their imaginations fed with 
 storybooks\, imaginative play\, and puppetry. Petite Mouse Takes a Nap is 
 her first children's book\, but she has more in mind.
LOCATION:Oxbow Public Market
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/907112011906470/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
