BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:White Evangelicalism: Unpacking the movement's history
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T210000
UID:260218OeRsR5lAI06zXvFpVyTbyg
DESCRIPTION:White Evangelicalism: Unpacking the movement’s history in or
 der to understand its influence on the country and culture today\n\nThursd
 ay\, March 26\, 7:00 pm\n\nThe Iona Lecture Series is where arts and scien
 ces meet humanity. In this Iona Lecture\, public theologian Cara Meredith 
 will trace the history of the white evangelical movement\, particularly in
  the 20th century\, in order to understand its influence on U.S. politics 
 and culture today. Her work highlights both the harm and the good\, partic
 ularly toward women\, people of color\, and the LGBTQ\\+ community\, and i
 s told through a storytelling lens of personal narrative\, Christian theol
 ogy\, and journalistic integrity.  \n\nJoin us for this important evenin
 g of conversation with lecture at 7 pm and wine and cheese reception to fo
 llow. \n\nFree and Open to the Public. \n\nAuthor\, freelance writer\, a
 nd public theologian Cara Meredith is passionate about collective liberati
 on\, mutual reciprocity\, and being a good neighbor. Her first book\, The 
 Color of Life: A Journey Toward Love and Racial Justice \\(Zondervan\, 201
 9\\)\, examines her journey as a white woman into issues of race after mar
 rying the son of Civil Rights icon James Meredith. Her second book\, Churc
 h Camp: Bad Skits\, Cry Night\, and How White Evangelicalism Betrayed a Ge
 neration \\(Broadleaf\, 2025\\)\, lends a critical eye to the place she lo
 ved and long called home\, with a particular lens toward injustices experi
 enced by women\, people of color\, and the LGBTQ\\+ community. She holds a
  master of theology from Fuller Seminary and is a postulant for Holy Order
 s in the Episcopal Church \\(Diocese of California\\)\, to be ordained Dea
 con in June 2026 and Priest in December 2026. With a background in educati
 on and nonprofit work\, she wears more hats than she probably ought\, but 
 mostly just enjoys playing with words\, a lot. She has been featured in na
 tional media outlets such as The Oregonian\, The New York Times\, The Livi
 ng Church\, The Christian Century\, and Baptist News Global\, among others
 . The Pacific Northwest native now lives in the San Francisco Bay Area wit
 h her husband and two sons.
LOCATION:St. Columba's Inverness
URL:https://www.stcolumbasinverness.org/iona-lecture-cara-meredith
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: Celebrating Women
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260326T180000
UID:260217n2n0K8iG1kmpWshbQ5OWAQ
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  2/13/26\n\n**MARCH EXHIBIT: CELE
 BRATING WOMEN**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  February 23 – March 29\, 2026\n\n**R
 ECEPTION: SATURDAY\, MARCH 7\, 2026\, 4-6 pm: Join in to meet the artists 
 and celebrate the show. Take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing 
 for a beautiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**
 \n\nSonoma County artist\, **Tosya Shore\,** presents **Celebrating Women\
 ,** paintings that commemorate women in honor of Women’s History Month. 
 Shore’s watercolor works capture women in their element\, showing the mu
 ltiple facets of their lives.  These dynamic paintings break away with st
 rong shapes and interlacing patterns that draw the viewer in exciting ways
 .  A la Degas\, we catch a ballet dancer lacing her shoes in “Good Poin
 t.”  The artist takes us into nature with “Redwood Rendezvous” wher
 e dominant trunk shapes frame a couple enjoying a glorious forest scene. 
    “Just Back from Vegas” captures a fleeting view of elegance as th
 e woman in question catches her breath.  “There’s such special feelin
 g in these everyday moments\, I love to turn the mundane into magic – wo
 men deserve nothing less\,” noted Shore. \n\nMeet the artist: Shore wil
 l be hosting the Gallery on March 5 and 19 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\n The Sta
 irway Smallworks Showcase features **Donna Schaffer’s Ooh La La\, Plein 
 Air\,** a collection unveiling oil paintings made on her recent trip to Fr
 ance.  Roaming the streets of Paris\, toting paints and palette\, Schaffe
 r captured iconic scenes buzzing with “la belle vie.” The viewer catch
 es a true cultural vibe in “Café le Bistro”\, the site of a favored h
 angout for espresso and conversation.  One is awed by the structure risin
 g from the ground-level trees in Schaffer’s unique view of the Eiffel To
 wer in “Paris is for Lovers.” “Every day was an adventure in Paris 
 – I hope through these plein air vignettes\, to share the excitement of 
 being there”\, stated Schaffer.\n\nMeet the artist: Schaffer will be hos
 ting the Gallery on March 21 and 22 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nUpstairs Art Gal
 lery\, 306 Center Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DA
 ILY: 11am – 6 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further 
 information: Contact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net o
 r 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
