BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Free Kombucha Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T130000
UID:260223hoPsdGmQTUygCYsVscB8gA
DESCRIPTION:Ready to brew your own delicious kombucha at home? Join us for
  this FREE workshop in partnership with Cultivate Community Food Co-Op and
  renowned Kombucha maker Ian Griffin\, where Ian will guide you through ev
 erything you need to know to become a confident kombucha maker! You'll lea
 rn the complete brewing process from start to finish\, beginning with F1 \
 \(First Fermentation\\) where you'll learn how to brew and sweeten the tea
 \, then Ian will demonstrate F2 \\(Second Fermentation\\) which covers bot
 tling and flavoring techniques. Learn the advantages and limitations of bo
 th Batch and Continuous Brew methods so you can choose what works best for
  you. The session will also include tips for setting up a "SCOBY Hotel"\\*
  to keep your brewing going strong. Attendees who are ready to dive in can
  leave with a SCOBY and starter liquid to begin their kombucha journey at 
 home. \\*A SCOBY Hotel is a glass jar where kombucha brewers store SCOBYs 
 \\(Symbiotic Cultures of Bacteria and Yeast\\) and starter liquid as a bac
 kup source for new brews. Bio: Ian Griffin is the publisher of Booch News\
 , where he has published over 400 articles about kombucha\, and the editor
  of SYMBIOSIS Magazine\, the Official Journal of Kombucha Brewers Internat
 ional. Over the past six years he has met with and interviewed dozens of c
 ommercial kombucha producers in Europe and the States. He has been an avid
  home brewer since 2010 and has taught classes on home brewing in San Fran
 cisco\, Berkeley\, and at his home in Vallejo. Free Register
LOCATION:The Exchange
URL:https://www.visitvallejo.com/events/upcoming-events/free-kombucha-work
 shop
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
